social_posts.post_text: …I think you look good Mrs. Armstrong👀

My face when I post about @jordinsparks birthday a day late….😅 Jordin HAPPY (late) BIRTHDAY! I was lucky to be involved in this crazy chapter of your life and made a lifelong friend out of it! Most people know you for being a insanely talented performer but I think what impresses me the most is your goofy, juice loving, Rick and Morty sock wearing self! You’re the best mom and wife for your family and it’s honestly something I’ll always look up too! 🙏🏽Anyways as always it’s all love and hope you have the best years to come! ❤️ 
From,
Belvis

We’re gonna tell our kids about this someday. 🤞🏼

Video by our insanely talented friend Dylan - @ambitcreative. We will forever be indebted to him for creating our wedding video so beautifully. We could say thank you a billion times but it will never be enough. 

Song by @thenationalparksband - “Angels”

Happy Valentine’s Day to the most beautiful, goofy and perfect girl! I love you and can’t wait to celebrate you forever! ♾️ I hope you feel celebrated everyday! Happy Valentine’s Day to everyone as well! Hopefully you are feeling love from your friends and family but most importantly I hope you are loving yourselves! ❤️❤️

social_posts.post_text:
Step 1: Finish an amazing tour ✔️
Step 2: Go on vacation with the wifey to @thewestinmaui ✔️
Step 3: Have a baby…..in a few years! 😂 👶🏾

Bry and sharks only have 1 thing in common….

they both prefer dark meat. 🍗 

Ate good food, was scared to go into the water, took a surf lesson and stayed at the best @thewestinmaui. It was definitely a perfect trip! 🌴

This was over 15 years ago. My first time dancing on TV. In a big city, with tons of unfamiliar people, pressure, expectations and all that come with it. It’s crazy because I still remember exactly how I felt then and this is because of people like Len. Now that I’m grown I still felt the same way every time I stood in front of him. Thank you Len for providing me and so many other dancers like me with an opportunity to show our talents. Whether you liked the dancing or not you were always kind and fair to me! You blessed my life with your voice for years and I’ll never forget that! Rest in peace my friend! ❤️

Just finished up celebrating my favorite person on the planet all weekend! Happy birthday to the wifey @bryleearmstrong_ If you are lucky enough to know her, you already know she’s the most thoughtful, loving and goofiest person ever! You’re the most important thing I have and I can’t wait to celebrate you every day forever! I love you the most and always ❤️❤️

With the big tour announcement we got today I figure it’s a good time to share one of my favorite dances from tour this year! Any chance I get to dance on stage is special for me but it is especially special when it’s with a dancer as amazing as @alexis_warr and in front of the best fans in the world! Without people in the audience showing love and energy it wouldn’t be such a great memory that I get to carry. So thank you guys! I miss this all the time and can’t wait to get back to it!

Also thanks to @robertroldan_ for the choreography and @nopenother for all the teaching you give me!
This is Bry’s audition for Dancing with the Stars…👀. Not too bad for her first time doing any ballroom!!! 👏🏽💃🏼

That was the fastest year of my life! Happy anniversary Bry. Looking back to this time last year I would have never expected to love you more than I did the day I married you but somehow I do! A lifetime of anniversaries still wouldn’t be enough with you! I love you always ❤️

The dream team was finally back together but this time on my home turf! And let me tell you, the people in Utah loveeee @jordinsparks! And she KILLED it! 

As good as it was seeing you again @jordinsparks - I’m still waiting for the invite to be on your next single but other than that you the best! 😉🙏🏽
Meet my season 32 partner! @lelepons let’s do this! I’m working on my Spanish so….VAMOSS !!! 🕺🏽💃🏼
Cheers to learning and making new friends! Can’t wait to see what @lelepons and @brandonarmstrong bring to #DWTS. 🎉
Hit New York for DWTS SEASON 32✨

How’s my Spanish after a month of rehearsals!?😂 LeLe is definitely better at dancing then I am at Spanish so I’m gonna  let her take the lead for Latin night!💃🏽 Make sure you vote by texting LeLe to 21523!

This was a WILD week! Thank you @dancingwiththestars for putting on such an important night! Being with Lele has shown me so much about the Latin culture here in America and I feel blessed to be welcomed into it! From the food and the music to the parties and friends this past few weeks has been filled with so many first for me and most of all so much LOVE! Thanks y’all! Lele you killed it as always!

LELE PONS! Tuesday night didn’t go the way we wanted to and that’s gonna happen. With so many eyes on you and everything you do it gets stressful trying to always be perfect. This show is all about showing growth and getting better each week! Now we have a chance to do that together. I’m proud of you, your family and friends are proud of you but most of all YOU should be proud of yourself! You’re incredible and I cant wait for another week to show it! Let’s get it! ❤️❤️

Disney100 night and it’s always my favorite! Super proud of all the work @lelepons did this week to get ready. 🕺🏽💃🏽

social_posts.post_text: Alright I still don’t think that I have all my thought’s together about this whole thing but even if I did I don’t think I’d be able to say them all…❤️ This season has been such a great time for me professionally but even better personally. I knew right when I met Lele that the two of us would be friends forever! From the first day when you almost ran me over with your car, to watching all your friends come and support you and of course all the crazy stuff you did everyday it’s been such a fun ride! 😂 Sucks that it ended early cause I feel like we had so many more memories to make but we definitely made some great ones. You worked so hard and cared so much that it pushed me to be better and I owe you for that! Hopefully I helped you fall in love with dance and can’t wait till we do it again! ❤️🙏🏽
Getting eliminated stings a little less now 😇  #dancingwiththestars #dwts #lelepons
Joking about it VS. it becoming a reality 😂🔥🙌🏼 @brandonarmstrong @dancingwiththestars

We are so thankful to call this @dancingwiththestars cast friends and family! Love y’all! ❤️🦃

social_posts.post_text: I can’t believe this season is over already! @lelepons you are the best! This season gave me some of my favorite times I’ve ever had on the show. You worked so hard, are so talented but most of all we laughed so much! I loved being able to go into “work” and enjoy myself personally and creatively. Being able to leave this season with someone who will always be my friend means the world! @bryleearmstrong_ and I love you like family! We are always thankful for the show but definitely a little extra this time. Also, huge congratulations to my boy @valentin and @_xochitl.gomez for an amazing season! Seeing y’all this season come in and consistently be amazing week after week was amazing to watch! Much love y’all and until next season! Love❤️
